Josto:
Mm...

15:52.185 --> 15:54.519
They filmed<i> casablanca</i>
in casablanca.

15:54.554 --> 15:56.521
-Hmm?
-Yeah.

15:56.556 --> 15:59.324
Oh, y-yeah, course. Silly me.

15:59.359 --> 16:02.260
Just-- doesn't it sound divine?

16:02.295 --> 16:05.496
Getting away, laying out
for the northern territories,

16:05.532 --> 16:07.498
wind in your hair?

16:09.469 --> 16:12.403
I got mouths to feed,
answerability.

16:12.439 --> 16:16.374
Oh. A box, you mean--
four walls of pine,

16:16.409 --> 16:18.343
which is...
(sighs)

16:18.378 --> 16:21.179
well, a coffin
is what it is, mister.

16:21.214 --> 16:23.514
There are places
in the amazon rainforests

16:23.550 --> 16:26.651
where a million butterflies
take flight all at once.

16:26.686 --> 16:29.620
Isn't that something a man
should see before he dies?

16:31.691 --> 16:34.525
My brother's in from the
old country, breaking balls.

16:34.561 --> 16:37.362
Ah, excuse you, mr. Potty mouth.

16:37.397 --> 16:38.663
Sorry.

16:38.698 --> 16:41.599
It's just-- I swear
I could kill that guy.

16:41.634 --> 16:43.601
-Your brother?
-No.

16:43.636 --> 16:45.336
Doctor at the hospital.

16:45.372 --> 16:47.271
Stuffed shirt,
thinks he shits cornflakes.

16:47.307 --> 16:48.473
Harvard.

16:50.410 --> 16:52.377
Goodness.

16:52.412 --> 16:55.179
Your mind's a clutter
of grievances.

16:57.217 --> 16:58.616
Here I am,
talking about waterfalls,

16:58.651 --> 17:02.453
and you're making
a list of nemeses.

17:02.489 --> 17:05.490
Friends or enemies.
That's the world, hmm?

17:05.525 --> 17:08.292
Oraetta mayflower's enemy
to no man.

17:08.328 --> 17:10.328
You're a dame.

17:10.363 --> 17:13.431
Where I come from,

17:13.466 --> 17:18.302
we sleep with one eye open
and a razor in our teeth.

17:18.338 --> 17:20.371
You got any more
of that fluffy whiz bang?

17:20.407 --> 17:22.373
Get my head on straight?

17:22.409 --> 17:25.276
And here I thought you liked me
for my vocabulary.

17:25.311 --> 17:27.545
Well, it's not your vocabulary
that just took a ride in my lap.

17:27.580 --> 17:29.380
Hey! That-- rude.

17:29.416 --> 17:32.583
We fly elevated
in this house, mister.

17:32.619 --> 17:34.652
Proper ladies and gentlemen,
which is a lesson

17:34.687 --> 17:37.422
you should take to heart
in your other lives.

17:37.457 --> 17:39.424
And you sleep
with a mouthful of razors,

17:39.459 --> 17:41.459
it's your own throat
that gets cut.

17:41.494 --> 17:42.560
Believe you me.

17:47.634 --> 17:50.134
You got the powder or not?

17:50.170 --> 17:51.469
<i> Oraetta:</i>
<i> I thought you were refined.</i>

17:51.504 --> 17:53.438
Why? 'cause my shoes are shiny?

17:58.511 --> 18:00.378
(sniffs)

18:00.413 --> 18:02.346
(groans softly)

18:02.382 --> 18:05.249
look at that. You left a mark.

18:05.285 --> 18:09.287
Mm. I'm sure I don't know
what you mean.

18:13.426 --> 18:15.159
What is this?

18:15.195 --> 18:16.394
Uh, sorry. I was...

18:16.429 --> 18:18.296
Is miss mayflower home?

18:18.331 --> 18:19.597
Oraetta:
Nobody wants you here.

18:19.632 --> 18:22.500
You said 50 cents or a dollar
for organizing.

18:22.535 --> 18:26.170
-I got to go.
-Well, d-don't,
you don't, don't...

18:32.312 --> 18:33.578
See what you did?

18:33.613 --> 18:36.314
Sorry. I just-- if you
need help with organizing,

18:36.349 --> 18:39.283
or anything...
(sighs)

18:39.319 --> 18:41.452
we need the money.

18:46.259 --> 18:48.493
(sighs)

18:48.528 --> 18:51.162
well, now, look at you.

18:51.197 --> 18:54.465
Sagittarius.

18:54.501 --> 18:57.401
I didn't recognize you
in this dark hallway.

18:57.437 --> 18:59.604
-You said...
-I did, but can it wait,
sweetie?

18:59.639 --> 19:02.173
Oraetta's got to get to work.

19:02.208 --> 19:04.208
I got time now.

19:04.244 --> 19:06.177
-I'm a good organizer.
-Oh...

19:06.212 --> 19:09.280
There's that gumption.

19:09.315 --> 19:11.282
Ah, fine.

19:11.317 --> 19:13.518
Come in while I get cleaned up.

19:24.631 --> 19:29.600
I'm usually oh, so organized,
but, well, these days my mind's

19:29.636 --> 19:33.504
like a little bird,
a million miles away.

19:33.540 --> 19:36.374
Oh, I've been reading about
the kings of egypt.

19:36.409 --> 19:38.609
Pharaohs, they're called.

19:38.645 --> 19:42.480
Like that king tut they found
living inside a pyramid.

19:42.515 --> 19:48.386
He's a mummy, so...
Dead, I think.

19:48.421 --> 19:50.288
Of course. Yeah.

19:50.323 --> 19:53.424
Well, no, he wasn't "living in,"
he was laying in.

19:53.459 --> 19:56.427
Why, sometimes my mouth says
just the strangest things.

19:56.462 --> 19:58.229
Oh, shoot. I've got to fly.

19:58.264 --> 19:59.564
Now, will you just
put some things away,

19:59.599 --> 20:01.566
so that when I come home tonight
I don't feel like

20:01.601 --> 20:04.235
jumping out the window
with everything such a jumble?

20:04.270 --> 20:06.637
Uh, do you want me
to wash these dishes?

20:06.673 --> 20:08.673
Oh, would you?
That'd be swell.

20:08.708 --> 20:12.310
Oh, and while you're at it,
my room's just down the hallway.

20:12.345 --> 20:15.479
So if you're doing dishes, you
might as well clean the sheets.

20:15.515 --> 20:17.582
(quietly):
Sheets.

20:19.452 --> 20:21.652
(door creaks, closes)

20:23.590 --> 20:26.357
-what's in there?
-Oh, never you mind about that.

20:26.392 --> 20:27.625
Now, like I said,

20:27.660 --> 20:30.428
there's, uh, there's
french-playing records

20:30.463 --> 20:32.697
just by the hi-fi, and, uh,

20:32.732 --> 20:36.334
yeah, you can borrow
any book you like.

20:36.369 --> 20:38.269
How much?

20:38.304 --> 20:39.470
How much what?

20:39.505 --> 20:41.539
The way I see it,
this whole place--

20:41.574 --> 20:44.442
sheets, dishes,
three hours' work--

20:44.477 --> 20:46.310
that's at least a dollar.

20:47.547 --> 20:50.581
Well, aren't you
a little capitalist.

20:57.357 --> 20:59.290
(antoon snoring)

21:01.628 --> 21:03.594
hey.

21:03.630 --> 21:05.663
What the hell
are you doing here?

21:05.698 --> 21:07.665
I got to tell you something.

21:07.700 --> 21:09.667
What?

21:12.672 --> 21:15.339
You're gonna hear talk,
about me,

21:15.375 --> 21:18.342
something I did
or maybe didn't do.

21:18.378 --> 21:19.644
Shining a bad light, I mean.

21:19.679 --> 21:21.646
Just be aware of whose lips
are doing the flapping.

21:21.681 --> 21:23.614
Are you being a fink? It sounds
like you're being a fink.

21:23.650 --> 21:27.551
-I botched a hit.
-You botched-- how's that?

21:27.587 --> 21:30.321
The cannon boy. Lemuel.

21:30.356 --> 21:32.490
Calamita said get in the car,
so I got in the car.

21:32.525 --> 21:34.392
We tailed the kid.
He said light him up.

21:34.427 --> 21:36.227
I'm sinking my teeth
into your jugular

21:36.262 --> 21:37.428
-if this story ends with...
-No, no, no. It don't.

21:37.463 --> 21:39.664
Like I said,
he told me to open up,

21:39.699 --> 21:41.632
but events didn't feel right.

21:41.668 --> 21:43.601
"on whose authority?" I ask him,

21:43.636 --> 21:46.337
but he don't say,
so I laid on the kibosh.

21:46.372 --> 21:48.339
But the kid saw my fangs,
no doubt.

21:48.374 --> 21:49.640
And look, look,
if you ordered it,

21:49.676 --> 21:51.509
I got no problem
accepting consequence.

21:51.544 --> 21:53.344
But I know you don't want
to start a war.

21:53.379 --> 21:55.246
I didn't order a goddamn hit!

21:57.283 --> 21:59.350
So you're saying what? Gaetano?

21:59.385 --> 22:02.219
You're telling me that porkpie,
ziti-eating greaser

22:02.255 --> 22:03.621
is giving my boys orders now?

22:03.656 --> 22:06.390
That sticky golem wop.

22:06.426 --> 22:07.525
(grunts)

22:07.560 --> 22:10.161
you gotta be kidding me!
(grunts)

22:11.597 --> 22:13.331
(shouts)

22:13.366 --> 22:15.266
(exhales)

22:19.505 --> 22:21.472
-(whistles)
-(grunts)

22:21.507 --> 22:23.474
-look. Here.
-(engine starts)

22:23.509 --> 22:26.210
you're a good boy. Reliable.

22:26.245 --> 22:27.411
-You're with me, right?
-Mm-hmm.

22:27.447 --> 22:29.647
All right.
You're gonna watch them.

22:29.682 --> 22:31.549
-Who?
-All of them.

22:31.584 --> 22:33.484
You're like a fucking bird
on a wire, got me?

22:33.519 --> 22:34.585
Eyes in the back of your head.

22:34.620 --> 22:36.687
What about calamita?

22:36.723 --> 22:40.224
Eh, don't worry, he'll get his.

22:40.259 --> 22:41.525
It's a new day. Got me?

22:41.561 --> 22:43.260
Spring fucking cleaning.

22:43.296 --> 22:45.596
You're either loyal,
or you're with him.

22:47.667 --> 22:49.400
Find that cop, odis.

22:49.435 --> 22:51.602
Tell him to come to the club,
rapid fire.

